 Port Elizabeth - Police in Port Elizabeth are seeking the assistance of the public in locating a missing 14-year-old boy from Motherwell. "The 14-year-old boy, Lisakhanya Siwani, was last seen on Friday, at around 05:30, by his grandmother when she left for work," described police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge. "On her return home in the evening, she discovered that the boy was not at home. "She searched for him at relatives and friends in the vicinity, but could not find him." Capt Beetge said that she continued with the search the next day, but after failing to locate the boy, she reported him missing to police later that day. "Any person that could assist police in finding the boy can contact the investigating officer, Detective Warrant Officer Riaan Krause at 071 352 4674 or 08600 10111." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  